==English==
===Etymology===
From the greek word ''pantheion'', a shrine to all the gods.
===Noun===
'''pantheon'''
#The totalality of gods of a given religion or culture.

===Proper Noun===
'''Pantheon'''
#The circular Roman temple dedicated to all the gods in 27 BC in Rome. Since the 7th century AD reconsecrated by christianity and dedicated to their single catholic god.

